  "description": "Gustaf Alfred Alde was a Swedish architect born on June 22, 1893 in Stockholm. He graduated from the School of Arts and Crafts in 1913 and studied in several countries in Europe during different periods. He specialized in ship interiors and interior design and worked as a consultant for various companies including the Swedish America Line, Nordstjernan Shipping Company, Broströmkoncernen, Götaverken Shipyard, and Kockums Mek. Verkst. A-B. He designed interiors for several ships including the m/s Stockholm (built in Italy) and the m/y Stella Polaris. He also designed commercial buildings and the Valand restaurant in Gothenburg and Eriksbergs Mek. Verkst. A-B's new office building in Gothenburg, Thordéns Publishing House in Uddevalla, and the new laboratory for Avesta Jernverks A-B in Avesta. Gustaf Alfred Alde was married to Alice Claeson in 1923 and had two children: Elizabeth and Louise." 
